<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-380-432  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 380 432.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  April 23 1990 v218 n17 p34(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ISDN gets global embrace; it may be slow out of the starting gatein the United States, but ISDN is gaining widespread popularity inEurope and the Pacific Rim. (integrated services digital network)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Saghafi, Massoud M.; Sheth, Jagdish N.; Mukherjee, Ananya.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Despite several years of standardization, deployment andpromotion, integrated services digital network (ISDN) has notreally taken hold in the US.andP;  And developments here contrast withdevelopments elsewhere.andP;  Europe and Pacific Rim countries, forexample, are rapidly adopting ISDN, and they have plans to evolveto broadband ISDN (BISDN) and subsequent technologies.andP;  Japan andSweden are positive toward ISDN and related technologies,especially fiber optics.andP;  Why is the evolution of an ISDN marketstill so tenuous in the US, while it is vigorous in other parts ofthe world? To answer this question, ISDN scenarios in variousparts of the world are examined.andP;  In the US, it is noted, vendors,carriers and users have participated in numerous ISDN trials, andcommercial services are slowly appearing.andP;  What is needed, it issaid, is an expansion of these processes.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TelecommunicationsTelephone systemsISDNOutlookTrendsInternational CommunicationsStandardizationUnited StatesEuropeJapan.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>